climbs.name: You Go Ahead and Clean It
climbs.fa: Pat Brennan and Jeff Brennan, October 2001

content.description: Climbs a bottom to top hand crack with a wide section at the beginning.
content.protection: Gear to 3 inches - there are bolted anchors near the finish of this route
content.location:
The next route right of

Tabby

.

climbs.name: White Paws
climbs.fa: Pat Brennan and Jeff Brennan, October 2001

content.description: A mostly hand crack that is steeper at the bottom and turns to twin cracks near the top.
content.location: This is the rightmost crack on the northwest face.

climbs.name: Tabby
climbs.fa: Pat Brennan and Jeff Brennan, October 2001

content.description: Face climb up into a hand crack that doesn't reach the ground.
content.location:
The next crack right of

Cat Claw

that starts about halfway up the face.

climbs.name: Midnight
climbs.fa: Pat Brennan and Jeff Brennan, October 2001

content.description: Climb a shallow right-facing corner capped by a small roof and then move slightly left into a thin crack that widens.
content.location: Just right of the obvious wide crack in the center of the wall.

climbs.name: Glucose and Fructose
climbs.fa: Pat Brennan and Jeff Brennan, October 2001

content.description: Climb a thin crack, passing a lower angled section and then finish in a hand crack.
content.location:
Around and right from

White Paws

on the east face.

content.description: Climb unprotected face into a thin crack that begins midway up the route.
content.location:
Located around and left from

Cat Claw

on the west face.

climbs.name: Enough Wasting Time
climbs.fa: Pat Brennan and Jeff Brennan, October 2001

content.description: A short but pleasant hand sized crack that passes along the right edge of a small roof/overlap near the midpoint.
content.location:
The next crack 4 feet right of

Midnight

.

climbs.name: Chinese
climbs.fa: Pat Brennan and Jeff Brennan, October 2001

content.description: Squirm and wiggle up the easy chimney, passing a constriction midway, with minimal gear but remember - you are the pro!
content.location: This is the obvious wide crack in the center of the face.

content.description: A nice mostly hand crack that splits into twin cracks just below the top.
content.location: This is the furthest left crack on the face.
